    <bug_when>2015-08-04 09:29:41 -0400</bug_when>
    <thetext>Description of problem:
ipcalculator doesn&apos;t accept IPv6 addresses. Given that IPv6 is already there, having tools to manipulate IP addresses without IPv6 support is an issue.


How reproducible:
$ ipcalculator ::1

Actual results:
INVALID ADDRESS: ::1


Expected results:
Information about the IPv6 address.

Additional info:
The fedora 23 ipcalc utility most likely deprecates that tool as it supports both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

$ ./ipcalc ::1
Full Address:	0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0001
Address:	::1
Address space:	Loopback Address</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
